.page-header
  %h1
    Map Module
%p
  The two mandatory elements for YAML files are the parser and map modules. The parser module is used when Avicore reads a YAML file. It needs to know when it was written so that it can use appropriate methods to understand outdated modules and features. The map module contains static variables such as the map name, version and authors.

:yaml
  map:
    name: "Map Name"
    version: 1.0.0
    authors:
    # KyloCode
    - uuid: 8242e55e-cc6a-458a-b272-a2b34918045f
      role: "YAML author."
    # Notch
    - uuid: 069a79f4-44e9-4726-a5be-fca90e38aaf5
      role: "Created Minecraft."

